ffice%2C%20Trump%20has%20been%20clear%20that%20he%20wants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-eliminate-education-department-executive-order-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eschools%20to%20align%20their%3C%2Fa%3E%20political%20ideologies%20with%20his%20own.%20Days%20after%20his%20inauguration%2C%20he%20signed%20executive%20orders%20to%20remove%20%26quot%3Bwoke%26quot%3B%20ideology%20from%20classrooms%20and%20expand%20the%20use%20of%20school%20vouchers.%20Both%20of%20these%20orders%20directed%20the%20education%20secretary%20to%20prepare%20guidance%20but%20did%20not%20yet%20require%20schools%20to%20comply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edozens%20of%20investigations%20into%20both%20K-12%20and%20higher%20education%20institutions%20are%20making%20those%20orders%20more%20real%2C%20with%20Trump%20stating%20that%20targeted%20schools%20can%20either%20accept%20his%20demands%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-rejects-trump-policy-demands-federal-funding-antisemitism-9-billion-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elose%20their%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20K-12%20side%2C%20Trump's%20administration%20has%20sent%20letters%20to%20school%20districts%20that%20it%20said%20have%20violated%20Title%20IX%20%E2%80%94%20a%20federal%20law%20that%20prohibits%20sex-based%20discrimination%20in%20education%20%E2%80%94%20through%20policies%20intended%20to%20accomodate%20transgender%20students%20that%20the%20administration%20describes%20as%20%26quot%3Brequiring%20girls%20in%20the%20school%20to%20share%20their%20locker%20room%20with%20a%20boy%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fabout%2Fnews%2Fpress-release%2Focr-launches-investigations-illinois-doe-chicago-public-school-district-299-and-deerfield-public-schools-district-109-over-reported-title-ix%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20higher%20education%20side%2C%20dozens%20of%20schools%20have%20received%20letters%20from%20the%20administration%20accusing%20them%20of%20violating%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Act%20through%20DEI%20initiatives%2C%20like%20allowing%20scholarships%20and%20network%20opportunities%20for%20minority%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFunding%20is%20on%20the%20line%20across%20the%20board%2C%20and%20while%20both%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20administrations%20have%20launched%20civil%20rights%20investigations%20into%20the%20country's%20schools%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ER.%20Shep%20Melnick%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20American%20politics%20at%20Boston%20College%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Trump's%20actions%20are%20at%20a%20much%20larger%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20types%20of%20gigantic%20threats%20are%20really%20quite%20new%2C%26quot%3B%20Melnick%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20no%20precedent%20for%20this%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it's%20well%20beyond%20anything%20in%20the%20words%20or%20the%20intention%20of%20a%20statute%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Education%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%20Craig%20Trainor%2C%20the%20department's%20acting%20assistant%20secretary%20for%20civil%20rights%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20February%2014%20%26quot%3BDear%20Colleague%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fmedia%2Fdocument%2Fdear-colleague-letter-sffa-v-harvard-109506.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20both%20K-12%20and%20higher%20education%20institutions%20that%20incorporate%20DEI%20will%20be%20flagged%20for%20%26quot%3Bdiscriminatory%20practices%26quot%3B%20subject%20to%20investigations%20and%20potential%20funding%20freezes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstitutions%20that%20fail%20to%20comply%20with%20federal%20civil%20rights%20law%20may%2C%20consistent%20with%20applicable%20law%2C%20face%20potential%20loss%20of%20federal%20funding%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20you%20been%20affected%20by%20Trump's%20proposed%20changes%20to%20education%2C%20or%20have%20any%20thoughts%20to%20share%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20asheffey.97.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221280fc6a-1b1d-4ad8-9534-26c8a5506f91%5C%22%3ESchool%20sports%20vs.%20federal%20funding%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20administration%20has%20so%20far%20launched%20dozens%20of%20investigations%20into%20school%20districts%20over%20DEI%20programming%2C%20transgender%20student%20policies%2C%20and%20antisemitism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20drastic%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eescalations%20has%20taken%20shape%20in%20Maine.%20What%20started%20as%20a%20public%20dispute%20between%20Maine's%20governor%20and%20Trump%20over%20the%20state%20allowing%20transgender%20athletes%20to%20play%20in%20women's%20school%20sports%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20major%20threat%20from%20the%20administration%20to%20cut%20off%20all%20of%20the%20state's%20federal%20funding%20for%20its%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20administration%20said%20that%20unless%20Maine%20complied%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fpresidential-actions%2F2025%2F02%2Fkeeping-men-out-of-womens-sports%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexecutive%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20restrict%20transgender%20students%20from%20women's%20sports%2C%20it%20would%20freeze%20the%20state's%20federal%20education%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efunding.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mainepublic.org%2Fpolitics%2F2025-03-15%2Frally-to-oppose-maines-policy-on-transgender-athletes-draws-crowd-in-augusta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Maine%20Principals'%20Association%2C%20there%20are%20only%20two%20transgender%20athletes%20competing%20in%20girls'%20high%20school%20sports%20statewide%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20court%20has%20already%20blocked%20the%20Trump%20administration%20from%20cutting%20school%20lunch%20funding%20over%20Maine's%20transgender%20policies.%20On%20Wednesday%2C%20Trump's%20Attorney%20General%20Pam%20Bondi%20announced%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20Maine%20to%20get%20the%20state%20to%20%26quot%3Bstop%20what%20they're%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaine's%20Gov.%20Janet%20Mills%20has%20vowed%20to%20continue%20fighting%20the%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20matter%20has%20never%20been%20about%20school%20sports%20or%20the%20protection%20of%20women%20and%20girls%2C%20as%20has%20been%20claimed%2C%20it%20is%20about%20states%20rights%20and%20defending%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20against%20a%20federal%20government%20bent%20on%20imposing%20its%20will%2C%20instead%20of%20upholding%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20Mills%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20school%20districts%20have%20been%20subject%20to%20similar%20investigations.%20The%20Minnesota%20State%20High%20School%20League%20and%20the%20California%20Interscholastic%20Federation%20received%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fabout%2Fnews%2Fpress-release%2Fus-department-of-education-launches-title-ix-investigations-two-athletic-associations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletters%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20the%20Trump%20administration%20stating%C2%A0that%20they%20would%20be%20investigated%20for%20%26quot%3Ballowing%20male%20athletes%20to%20compete%20in%20women's%20sports%20and%20use%20women's%20intimate%20facilities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20Oregon%20School%20Activities%20Association%20is%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fabout%2Fnews%2Fpress-release%2Foffice-civil-rights-launches-title-ix-investigations-portland-public-schools-and-oregon-school-activities-association%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20its%20policy%20that%20allows%20students%20to%20participate%20in%20sports%20or%20activities%20using%20their%20preferred%20gender%20identity%20while%20%26quot%3Bproviding%20a%20fair%20and%20safe%20environment%20for%20all%20students.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287c61c56-6819-45d5-9f3b-f3ee34261312%5C%22%3EWhat's%20next%20for%20US%20schools%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMelnick%20said%20that%20both%20former%20presidents%20Barack%20Obama%20and%20Joe%20Biden%20made%20frequent%20use%20of%20investigations%20through%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20to%20achieve%20their%20goals.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20opened%20over%20100%20new%20investigations%20in%20its%20first%20few%20weeks%20into%20racial%20and%20gender%20discrimination%2C%20and%20it%20was%20something%20Republicans%20criticized%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20remarkable%20is%2C%20despite%20all%20that%20Republicans%20have%20criticized%2C%20they%20have%20taken%20those%20initiatives%20and%20exploded%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Melnick%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20is%20all%20lawless.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20ongoing%20investigations%2C%20Melnick%20said%20that%20it's%20not%20unusual%20for%20an%20administration%20to%20conduct%20compliance%20reviews%2C%20which%20ensure%20schools%20are%20complying%20with%20civil%20rights%20laws.%20What's%20unusual%20here%20is%20the%20nature%20and%20extent%20of%20Trump's%20investigations%3B%20while%20reviews%20can%20drag%20out%20for%20years%2C%20Trump's%20administration%20is%20acting%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigher%20education%20institutions%20have%20faced%20similar%20threats%20from%20the%20administration%2C%20with%20Trump%20freezing%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20federal%20funding%20at%20schools%2C%20including%20Harvard%2C%20for%20refusing%20to%20meet%20the%20administration's%20demands%2C%20one%20of%20which%20was%20conducting%20an%20%26quot%3Baudit%26quot%3B%20of%20students%20and%20faculty%20to%20determine%20their%20ideological%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForty-five%20other%20colleges%2C%20including%20Arizona%20State%20University%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Utah%2C%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Rhode%20Island%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eare%20under%20investigation%20over%20accusations%20they%20violated%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Act%20by%20partnering%20with%20%26quot%3BThe%20Ph.D%20Project%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20provides%20networking%20and%20career%20opportunities%20for%20business%20students%20from%20underrepresented%20backgrounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20encourage%20open%20debate%20on%20campuses%20and%20different%20points%20of%20view%2C%20that's%20what%20education%20is%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20Education%20Secretary%20Linda%20McMahon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FEDSecMcMahon%2Fstatus%2F1912630708717384034%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20have%20civil%20rights%20trampled%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelnick%20said%20he%20expects%20the%20investigations%20to%20continue%2C%20and%20the%20question%20is%20how%20much%20schools%20choose%20to%20comply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20sense%20is%20that%20the%20amount%20of%20litigation%20is%20going%20to%20increase%20because%20I%20think%20that%20the%20administration%20is%20going%20to%20lose%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20court%20suits%2C%20and%20the%20more%20they%20lose%2C%20the%20more%20other%20schools%20will%20be%20encouraged%20to%20fight%20rather%20than%20to%20comply%2C%26quot%3B%20Melnick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20asheffey.97.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-reshaping-americas-schools-investigations-funding-cuts-department-of-education-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745136902000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ffbe0ca466d2b74ab34c69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-reshaping-americas-schools-investigations-funding-cuts-department-of-education-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20has%20launched%20investigations%20into%20K-12%20and%20higher%20education%20institutions%20as%20part%20of%20his%20mission%20to%20align%20the%20US%20school%20system%20with%20his%20politics.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-reshaping-americas-schools-investigations-funding-cuts-department-of-education-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20Neetu%20revealed%20why%20Ranbir-Deepika%20broke%20up%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745136824000%2C%22visual%22%3